        "created_at": "2024-07-29T19:19:18.869Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi everyone.<br>\nI am trying to relink my laptop to Signal, but it isn’t working. When I go to “Linked devices” and click “Link a new device”, I get a prompt to “Unlock to link a device - Enter your current PIN.”<br>\nI have input my PIN several times but the app wouldn’t accept it. So I changed my PIN, thinking maybe I’d misremembered what it was. But still, no dice. I just changed my PIN a second time, just in case, in vain. It just keeps saying “Try Again”.<br>\nI also updated the app (v 7.11.4).<br>\nI’m at a loss on what to do. Is this a bug? Or, because I changed my PIN, do I need to wait for something to happen in the backend to update my PIN before trying it? Any troubleshooting/advice would be really appreciated. I want to make sure I’ve tried everything before I make an official bug report on the github.</p>",
